headline: Wall Street Gains, Tech Rallies, Tesla Hits All-Time High As Inflation Data Firms Up Fed's Next Interest Rate Cut
summary: Wall Street kicked off Wednesday on a positive note as November inflation data came in line with expectations, leaving traders confident in the likelihood of a Federal Reserve interest rate cut next week. The Consumer Price Index rose 2.7% year-over-year in November, slightly above October's 2.6% annual rate, but perfectly aligned with economist forecasts. Core inflation, which excludes volatile categories like food and energy, remained flat at an annual rate of 3.3%, also meeting expectations.
